The paper deals with the problem of single-image super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of recurrent residual blocks and deep recurrence learning, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of multilevel fusion structures, which is a technique used in image processing (cs.MM). The use of transposed convolution instead of bicubic interpolation is a technique used in generative models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of fewer parameters, which is a topic commonly discussed in neural networks (cs.NE).
